parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brake pedal to become hard or go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS warning light appears on the dashboard
the brake pedal becomes hard or goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop or does not stop when the brakes are applied
the brakes malfunction or fail to engage
the ABS system engages unnecessarily under normal braking conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the brakes to malfunction or fail to engage, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes do not engage or respond slowly
the vehicle takes longer to stop or does not stop when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake system can cause the brakes to fail or malfunction, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes do not stop the vehicle when applied
the brakes take longer to stop the vehicle
the brakes malfunction or fail to engage
the ABS system engages unnecessarily under normal braking conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, posing a significant safety risk.
symptoms: The engine shuts down while driving
often at high speeds
without warning
and may not restart immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning electric door locks can cause inconvenience, difficulty in entering or exiting the vehicle, and potentially lead to safety issues if the doors become stuck or inoperable.
symptoms: The electric door locks drain the battery
fail to open or close
and may require manual operation
causing difficulties for the driver and passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The alternator fails
causing the battery to drain
and may result in engine stalling
dim or flickering headlights
and other electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Independent Strut Suspension Arrangement Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear independent strut suspension arrangement can cause the loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: The left rear fork collapses
the left rear wheel rim jams
the wheel is unable to rotate in either direction
unusual noises or vibrations from the rear suspension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front lower control arm can cause the loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations from the front suspension
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the steering feels loose or unstable.
